cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM

This paper deals with audio source separation using deep learning techniques. The focus is on optimizing sequence model architectures such as 1D-CNNs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also discusses the use of dense connections and dilated convolutions, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approaches on a test dataset, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
